00:45:08.010 --> 00:45:09.610
FLOYD ABRAMS: I should say
first, you have to agree with

00:45:09.610 --> 00:45:10.080
me, though.

00:45:10.080 --> 00:45:10.932
[LAUGHTER]

00:45:10.932 --> 00:45:12.640
FLOYD ABRAMS: Right?

00:45:12.640 --> 00:45:15.960
AUDIENCE: So I actually wanted
to ask you sort of a follow up

00:45:15.960 --> 00:45:20.135
question about the
Yale law student.

00:45:20.135 --> 00:45:21.540
FLOYD ABRAMS: Yeah.

00:45:21.540 --> 00:45:24.380
AUDIENCE: It's really less a
First Amendment question than

00:45:24.380 --> 00:45:27.120
sort of just your views about
the privacy issue involved.

00:45:27.120 --> 00:45:29.180
Because I think sometimes these
issues get a little

00:45:29.180 --> 00:45:30.670
muddled in people's minds.

00:45:30.670 --> 00:45:33.650
So if we sort of walk the cat
back a little bit there and we

00:45:33.650 --> 00:45:39.340
just take the situation where
the student's in college and

00:45:39.340 --> 00:45:44.550
makes statements on some
website, although with a

00:45:44.550 --> 00:45:48.750
anonymous name about, you know,
I'd rather go to Yale

00:45:48.750 --> 00:45:51.390
than Harvard because I think
Harvard Law School stinks and

00:45:51.390 --> 00:45:52.430
Yale's much better, right?

00:45:52.430 --> 00:45:55.040
And then ultimately, she winds
up getting into Harvard

00:45:55.040 --> 00:45:56.340
instead of Yale.

00:45:56.340 --> 00:46:00.530
And some, whether it's the
person on that website or

00:46:00.530 --> 00:46:03.130
somebody else, tracks down
this public, although

00:46:03.130 --> 00:46:07.330
anonymous, statement, and also
through non-criminal means,

00:46:07.330 --> 00:46:10.810
determines that this person is
now a student at Harvard and

00:46:10.810 --> 00:46:12.920
puts the two of those together
and publishes that

00:46:12.920 --> 00:46:14.580
information.

00:46:14.580 --> 00:46:16.440
I mean I don't think
there's a privacy

00:46:16.440 --> 00:46:17.800
expectation there, right?

00:46:17.800 --> 00:46:20.550
Because they put all that
information out there.

00:46:20.550 --> 00:46:22.550
But I'm just curious as to
whether you agree, or not.

00:46:22.550 --> 00:46:23.730
FLOYD ABRAMS: No, I agree.

00:46:23.730 --> 00:46:26.260
But there is a libel one if they
